Why Did You Return to Iron Maiden?
In: "Because It Was a Huge Opportunity " Out: "... Premier League Is Something You're Not Gonna Turn Down."
You Are Renowned for Your Huge Range of Activities - Fencing, Flying, Running Your Own Label Etc - Have You Had to Put Them on the Backburner?
In: "Yes I Get Up Every Morning..." Out: "... I'm Pretty Relaxed About Things Actually"
The 1999 Ed Hunter Tour Was an Enormous Sell-Out Success. What Made You Tour Before Recording the New Record?
In: "I Suppose We Wnted to Go..." Out: "... Add a Little Bit of Drama."
How Have Relationships Within the Band Changed Over the Passage of Time?
In: Basically, I Mean We Are All Still the Same People..." Out: "... What We Really Do Want to Do With the Record, Which Is Great."
In: "The Enthusiasm Factor..." Out: "... This Is Like the First Time Again You Know."
How Did You Feel About Performing Maiden Songs That Were Recorded Outside of Your Time From the Band?
In: "I Don't Have a Problem With Singing Maiden Songs..." Out: "... As Long as It Fits in the Set. We Shall See."
What's the Reaction to the New Line-Up?
"Well the New Line Up Was Going Down Terrific. Especially With Me!"
Are the Logistics of Touring Easier Now?

In: "A Little Bit I Suppose I'm Not Really Sure How the Dynamics of the Band..." Out: "... That's the Aim of the Whole Deal for Everyone to Get What They Want and Go Out and Have a Great Time Every Night."
What Are Your Thoughts on Earl Court Event & Touring the UK?
In: "Earls Court Is Obviously Going to Be a Highlight..." Out: "... It's Actually the Same Kind of Vibe It's Still British Rail Sandwiches!"
Which Bands Are You Taking Out With You on the Metal 2000 Tour and Why?
In: "We've Got Everybody From Korn, to Slayer Supporting Us..." Out: "... I Just Want All of Them to Try."
What Can Iron Maiden Accomplish in the Year 2000?
In: "We Want to Start by Regaining..." Out: "... I Just See Iron Maiden as Being an Antidote to the Crap"
What Was the Ed Hunter Tour Like?
In: "Yeah It Was Great Doing the Ed Hunter Thing..." Out: "... But It Still Sounds Live Which You Know Is the Best for Both Worlds"
